,0.01989597,-0.02088326,0.01947960,0.04318634,-0.06222307,0.10665639,0.04243434,-0.03949891,0.00226646,0.07586365,-0.01413437,0.03119009,-0.05221844,-0.04631036,0.00245733,0.03069507,0.04084945,-0.06922079,0.04602227,-0.02155901,-0.01647799,0.02271790,-0.00934600,0.01003809,-0.08054443,-0.05026314,0.02660046,-0.02521360,-0.01078005,-0.01698605,-0.01094063,0.03757326,-0.01865265,-0.00322111,0.02462725,-0.02045716,0.02921622,0.00040179,-0.02885352,0.07761358,0.07495645,0.00362022]',E'Hono - _**means flame🔥 in Japanese**_ - is a small, simple, and ultrafast web framework built on Web Standards. It works on any JavaScript runtime: Cloudflare Workers, Fastly Compute, Deno, Bun, Vercel, AWS Lambda, Lambda@Edge, and Node.js.\n\nFast, but not only fast.\n\n```ts\nimport { Hono } from ''hono''\nconst app = new Hono()\n\napp.get(''/'', (c) => c.text(''Hono!''))\n\nexport default app\n```','{"source": "hono", "version": "4", "language": "typescript", "title": "Readme", "section_title": "README", "url": "https://github.com/honojs/hono/blob/main/README.md", "topics": "hono,edge,http,README", "categories": "web,typescript,rest,edge"}');
